                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/663: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-22T18:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 22, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>39. Brazilian Minister for Foreign Affairs personally and confidentially informed
                    this afternoon of the contents of the Department’s telegram number 50, August
                    21, 6 p.m., and stated that his Government would be glad to cooperate fully
                    along the lines suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
